HEADWORD: Anonymity
<hw>An`o*nym"i*ty</hw>, <pos>n.</pos> <def>The quality or state of being
anonymous; anonymousness; also, that which anonymous.</def>
<mark>[R.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>He rigorously insisted upon the rights of
<qex>anonymity</qex>.</q> <rj><qau>Carlyle.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Anonymous</ent>⟦br⟧
